<br>
GFay -- no conclusion. I cant understand what the heck the elves are saying still. Maybe one day I will. Only when I understand them will I know if they RP or not. <br>
<br>
Gnomes -- only a handful of us Gnomes will bother to RP. The rest seem to be casual (tho polite) and seemingly new EQ players. So long as they are polite, I have no problem with this. Then again.... there is no &quot;easy template&quot; for RPing a Gnome.... because Gnomes can be anything....from the silly to good natured to downright sinister.... and in my case &quot;discordant naughty&quot;. <br>
<br>
Dwarves -- oh yes I must admit, I have run into a LOT of role playing Dorfs. Especially the Paladin Dorfs... they bow at me, and say things like Hail and Well Met Friend or &quot;Good Day Sir&quot;.... and all the really cheesy Renaissance England entrapment. So yes the Dorf Paladins are notorious for their cheesy &quot;I am a knight in shining armor&quot; type of role playing.... it gets to the point that it's downright annoying to an evil necromancer as myself. But I give them an A+ for effort.  <br>
<br>
I can understand some Dwarvish... so the role playing does come through to me as far as Dwarves go. <br>
<br>
Humans -- not sure, I cant quite speak their language yet. <br>
<br>
Teir'Dals -- no clue, but I get an awful lot of glares, jeers, and other negative emotes from the DEs. I'm not sure if they are role playing when they are tring to 'demean' a Gnome like myself..... or maybe they simply have a cork stuck up their butts.  No clue. Maybe once I learn their language I can finally tell. <br>
<br>
Iksar -- yeah I see them all the time in the Ro Desert and sometimes they zip along the East Commonlands. I have never seen one stop for 10 seconds to talk or role play. They always seem to be on the run, never having a moment for RPing or chit chat...... I can't blame them. Maybe they are too scared to stop for one second for fear that Sergeant Slate might come by and give them a smacking. My guess is that the Iksar tend to do most of their RPing in Kunark. <br>
<br>
Troll -- I dont see very much. But I have met 2 that role played. I cant understand them... but one troll at first was ridiculing me.... he points at me and then he does the /hungry emote..... basically telling me that I am his lunch, etc. Then he sees me conjure up my skeleton pet. So now he becomes all friendly knowing I'm a necromancer. He's a shaman, so he ends up showering me with buffs. I concluded he is an evil-align role player type.... since he recognized a fellow evil kindred upon seeing that I was a necro. This is perfectly good role playing as far as Im concerned. Maybe one day I might understand Trolls and Trolls might understand me. <br>
<br>
The Trolls might find it amusing to be able to speak with their food.  *grin*<br>
<br>
